Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.02,0:00:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, well...you've found\Nsome wonderful property.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.83,0:00:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a convenient twenty-minute drive\Nfrom the center of Berlin;
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.20,0:00:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,in a well-located\Nand nice neighborhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.50,0:00:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's rare to find this sort of property\Non the former East side.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.31,0:00:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Umm...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.51,0:00:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Wasn't this the residence\Nof Mr. Liebert,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.55,0:00:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the consultant to the former\NEast German Trade Commission?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.15,0:00:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.55,0:00:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,What? You just came\Nto investigate Mr. Liebert?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.62,0:00:42.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that all?! You're not a customer?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.36,0:00:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry... There was something\NI just had to find out.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.26,0:00:51.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't know anything about\Nan official who died ten years ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.17,0:00:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The Lieberts adopted twins\Nwhile they were here.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.97,0:00:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you, I don't know anything...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.48,0:01:00.67,Default,,0,0,0,,What about the landlord?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.21,0:01:02.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you introduce me to him?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.08,0:01:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen...most of the land in\Nthe former East side is the property
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.22,0:01:09.34,Default,,0,0,0,,of Jewish capitalists who escaped\Nfrom the Nazi regime.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.52,0:01:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The eastern government was paying\Nforeign countries and capitalists
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.39,0:01:15.55,Default,,0,0,0,,from the west side\Nand borrowing land.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.03,0:01:17.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The landlord for this property\Nis overseas...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.49,0:01:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, my company is\Na west-side real estate company
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.83,0:01:23.70,Default,,0,0,0,,that prospered after\Nthe destruction of the Wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.20,0:01:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know anything about the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.94,0:01:29.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, get out.\NI'm going to lock the gate...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.34,0:01:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,isn't there anyone who knows\Nabout ten years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.64,0:01:34.70,Default,,0,0,0,,someone who\Nremembers Mr. Liebert?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.35,0:01:39.41,Default,,0,0,0,,As I told you, this is a residential area\Nfor ex-government officials.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.15,0:01:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Most fled after the Wall came down.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.65,0:01:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Especially from the officials from\Nthe Ministry of the interior...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.96,0:01:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! Come to think of it...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.06,0:01:54.43,Default,,0,0,0,,An ex-official of the former East German\NDepartment of Commerce
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.53,0:01:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,lives ten houses away from here...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.57,0:02:02.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Mr. Liebert. He didn't have to\Ntake such a risk, only to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.71,0:02:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,If only he had waited\Njust a little longer,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.01,0:02:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,until East Germany collapsed...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.78,0:02:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It makes you wonder why\Nhe went to a free country...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.61,0:02:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Just to be killed of all things...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.48,0:02:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Did Mr. Liebert have twins?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.22,0:02:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Twins?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.82,0:02:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I remember!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.93,0:02:26.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Those twins that Mr. Liebert adopted\Nfrom the orphanage!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.03,0:02:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Orphanage?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.70,0:02:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,They were such cute kids...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.00,0:02:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Liebert always wanted children.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.14,0:02:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,W-Where is that orphanage?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.34,0:02:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Umm... I think it was...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.14,0:02:40.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm... 511 ?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.71,0:02:45.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's right,\NI think it was 511 Kinderheim...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.65,0:02:49.62,Default,,0,0,0,,511 ...Kinderheim?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.78,0:05:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The site of this orphanage will soon\Nbe turned into a supermarket.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.22,0:05:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm relieved that this creepy building\Nis finally going to be destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.73,0:05:47.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, do you know anyone\Nfrom this orphanage?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.70,0:05:50.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone from here?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.50,0:05:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,There isn't anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.10,0:05:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to talk about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.84,0:05:59.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It's so creepy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.31,0:06:00.33,Default,,0,0,0,,B-But...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.68,0:06:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,If you really want to find out,\Nthere's Hartmann over on 47th St.,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.48,0:06:08.54,Default,,0,0,0,,who worked at the old\NMinistry of Health and Welfare.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.17,0:06:31.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey there... Do you know someone\Nnamed Hartmann who lives around here?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.18,0:06:37.15,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.38,0:06:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You're injured... Let me take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.62,0:06:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all right. Don't be afraid.\NLet me take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.42,0:06:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You've injured a healing wound...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.93,0:06:50.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It's festering.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.83,0:06:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Suck it up!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.90,0:06:54.69,Default,,0,0,0,,This will sting a little,\Nbut this will help you get better.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.34,0:07:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, that's good...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.95,0:07:09.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't trip!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.68,0:07:11.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll get hurt again!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.89,0:07:18.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Hartmann...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.21,0:07:44.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I became the foster parent to all those\Nkids after the fall of East Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.58,0:07:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Foster parent?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.68,0:07:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I took care of them until they\Nwere adopted or went off on their own.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.49,0:07:54.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The president of\Nan accessories company
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.89,0:07:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,adopted the kid in the middle.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.13,0:07:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The kid to the left\Nis in the military right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.33,0:08:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm even taking care of one right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.87,0:08:05.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It must be hard work.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.67,0:08:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't call it work.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.57,0:08:13.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I worked for many years,\Ndealing with orphans,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.08,0:08:15.01,Default,,0,0,0,,as the district official for\Nthe Ministry of Health and Welfare.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.34,0:08:18.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I opposed the way that the government\Nwas treating them at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.08,0:08:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,After the fall of socialism, I wanted to\Nhelp the children in my own way.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.39,0:08:30.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm poor and things\Nhaven't gone my way...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.29,0:08:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,but, still, it's much better than\Nthe orphanages that they were in.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.70,0:08:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,511 Kinderheim was\Na special orphanage
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.80,0:08:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,that was run by both\Nthe Ministry of Health and Welfare
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.40,0:08:42.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and the Ministry of the interior.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.57,0:08:49.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, all orphanages in East Germany\Nwere more or less like that,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.01,0:08:54.04,Default,,0,0,0,,but special orphanages\Nwere the worst of them all...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.12,0:08:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn't just an institution\Nfor children with nowhere to go...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.62,0:09:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a gathering for\Nthe children of criminals,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.73,0:09:06.74,Default,,0,0,0,,captured political offenders,\Nand the children of those
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.76,0:09:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,suspected of being rebels and spies.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.97,0:09:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why it was expected that\Nthey would be discriminated against
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.27,0:09:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and treated inhumanely...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.67,0:09:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The children there couldn't do\Nanything about their situation...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.48,0:09:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a clash between socialism\Nand totalitarianism...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.08,0:09:30.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The government told the public that\Nthe orphans would be reeducated
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.55,0:09:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and turned into model socialists.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.49,0:09:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,But in reality,\Nthey were treated like criminals.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.86,0:09:37.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The directors and instructors\Nwere horrible...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.20,0:09:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The worst ones would confiscate\Npackages sent to the children
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.80,0:09:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and sell them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.60,0:09:46.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Who were the real criminals?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.00,0:09:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Fear and violence ruled\Nthe special orphanages.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.71,0:09:55.47,Default,,0,0,0,,No person would grow up\Nnormal there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.71,0:10:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Then that incident happened...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.92,0:10:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,incident?\NWhat happened at that orphanage?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.19,0:10:08.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You said that you wanted to\Nask me about the twins, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.89,0:10:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know something about them?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.13,0:10:15.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know much about the sister\Nbecause she was left at an orphanage
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.43,0:10:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,in a different district.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.83,0:10:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,But I do know about\Nthe brother, Johan.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.10,0:10:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Johan! Yes, I want to\Nknow about Johan!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.01,0:10:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It was...It was top secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.72,0:10:38.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The East German government\Nplaced a strict gag order on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.76,0:10:43.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it was a long time ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.56,0:10:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's all right to talk about it...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.26,0:10:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,What is this incident?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.27,0:10:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,What did...What did Johan do?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.27,0:10:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,A revolt...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.61,0:11:05.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm home...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.12,0:11:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Dieter, we have a guest.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.18,0:11:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Come and greet him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.89,0:11:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.02,0:11:13.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Dieter, what's with your attitude?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.32,0:11:15.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Aren't you going to greet him?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.13,0:11:19.39,Default,,0,0,0,,L-It's okay. We already met\Nin front of the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.33,0:11:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.40,0:11:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh...I'd like to hear the rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.34,0:11:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.44,0:11:29.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Not in front of the child.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.64,0:11:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh...you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.34,0:11:34.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It's already late so we should\Nmeet another day.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.65,0:11:38.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Dieter!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.85,0:11:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you care to\Nhave dinner with us?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.25,0:11:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,S-Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.66,0:11:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Tenma, you say that\Nyou're a freelance journalist.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.57,0:11:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Does that mean that you're going to\Nwrite an article about the things
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.37,0:12:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,that you've investigated?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.07,0:12:02.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.91,0:12:06.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, this is one thing\NI want you to emphasize...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.98,0:12:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The development of a child
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.21,0:12:11.54,Default,,0,0,0,,all depends on the adult\Nthat raises him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.92,0:12:16.25,Default,,0,0,0,,We must lead children\Nin the right direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.62,0:12:22.49,Default,,0,0,0,,That's when children can\Nhave pleasant dreams.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.23,0:12:24.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Dreams, huh-?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.03,0:12:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Dieter, what dreams do you have?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.33,0:12:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,A soccer ball...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.70,0:12:32.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh--?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.20,0:12:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I want a soccer ball!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.74,0:12:36.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.94,0:12:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.64,0:12:42.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to continue where we left off\Nanother time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.25,0:12:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry we couldn't\Nfinish our conversation.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.05,0:12:50.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll come again.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.42,0:12:51.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps I can come tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.50,0:13:04.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Dieter...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.43,0:13:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Umm... Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.30,0:13:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I come in?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.95,0:13:51.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Hartmann!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.35,0:13:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.45,0:13:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Hartmann!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.92,0:13:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Hartmann! Mr. Hartmann!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.09,0:14:01.25,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened, Mr. Hartmann!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.79,0:14:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Hartmann...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.79,0:14:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,M-Mr. Tenma...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.80,0:14:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Dieter!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.90,0:14:12.87,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.00,0:14:13.97,Default,,0,0,0,,He fell.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.70,0:14:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,He was standing on the chair and...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.11,0:14:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Dieter.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.81,0:14:21.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Ow...ow, it hurts...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.81,0:14:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Where does it hurt, Dieter?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.61,0:14:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It hurts...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.61,0:14:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Hartmann, call an ambulance!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.22,0:14:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,O-Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.99,0:14:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Dieter, let me take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.52,0:14:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,What are all these scars?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.70,0:14:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.43,0:14:42.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Does it hurt here?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.33,0:14:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Two ribs are broken...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.43,0:14:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And his clavicle is dislocated.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.20,0:14:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,How did he get this injury\Nfrom falling off a chair?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.44,0:14:56.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The ambulance will be here soon,\Nso it's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.25,0:14:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,O-Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.65,0:15:00.14,Default,,0,0,0,,But what are all these injuries?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.55,0:15:01.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you that it's all right...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.58,0:15:04.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.49,0:15:05.45,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.55,0:15:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The way you touch those injuries...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.69,0:15:10.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It's as if you're a doctor...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.89,0:15:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh...well...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.80,0:15:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Tenma...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.06,0:15:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought I heard\Nthat name somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.37,0:15:18.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a doctor, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.10,0:15:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the one wanted for murder...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.61,0:15:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,This injury...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.41,0:15:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are all these injuries\Non his body from?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.18,0:15:33.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Nevermind that... Shouldn't you\Nbe running away, Mr. Tenma?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.32,0:15:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I called the police\Nalong with the ambulance...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.92,0:15:41.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Hartmann! I'm asking you\Nhow Dieter got all these injuries!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.52,0:15:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It shouldn't matter\Nto someone like you,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.29,0:15:47.70,Default,,0,0,0,,who's wanted for murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.30,0:15:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just as I expected from a fugitive.\NYou're very short-tempered.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.54,0:15:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You did it, didn't you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.44,0:15:59.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Did it? Did what?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.64,0:16:02.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You were abusing Dieter.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.08,0:16:04.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Abusing?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.45,0:16:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't say such ill willed things\Nabout me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.45,0:16:08.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, Dieter?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.26,0:16:14.35,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you plan to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.09,0:16:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to take him to the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.39,0:16:19.95,Default,,0,0,0,,First murder, and now kidnapping?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.40,0:16:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't move!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.46,0:16:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll be caught even if you do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.97,0:16:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all right, Dieter! I'm going to\Nget you to a hospital!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.21,0:16:37.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm afraid of the hospital...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.11,0:16:39.08,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing to be afraid of!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.52,0:16:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The doctors will get you better.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.72,0:16:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Hartmann always\Nmakes me better...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.23,0:16:56.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You're covered in injuries...\NYou've never been to a hospital?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.73,0:17:02.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm afraid... Right now,\Nthe world is full of bad things.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.57,0:17:06.94,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I have to be strong!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.84,0:17:08.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Strong...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.28,0:17:10.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Did Mr. Hartmann tell you that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.08,0:17:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The world is dark...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.38,0:17:14.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The future is dark...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.86,0:17:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not true!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.39,0:17:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a big lie that the world is dark!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.39,0:17:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Really?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.76,0:17:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, it's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.40,0:17:29.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I forgot.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.77,0:17:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Here... A soccer ball.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.40,0:17:33.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.30,0:17:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomorrow will be...a good day.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.08,0:17:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry for coming at this hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.68,0:17:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all right... But we're crowded with\Nemergency cases at the moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.09,0:17:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It might take a while\Nuntil we can see him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.52,0:17:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Could you do something about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.52,0:17:57.39,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a very big accident.\N-The bus driver died instantly.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.73,0:18:00.99,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to ask the truck driver about\Nthe circumstances of the accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.46,0:18:03.69,Default,,0,0,0,,He broke both his legs,\Nbut he can still talk, can't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.37,0:18:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to treat him first.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.44,0:18:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Question him later.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.97,0:18:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, we'll be waiting here.\N-U-Umm...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.08,0:18:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be back in two hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.68,0:18:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.98,0:18:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Please take care of that boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.38,0:18:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, please don't let anyone\Nleave with him other than myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.69,0:18:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,U-Umm...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.59,0:18:31.15,Default,,0,0,0,,ls the accident site cleaned up?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.39,0:18:33.16,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's still backed up...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.30,0:18:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Now then...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.77,0:18:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,What should I do now?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.60,0:18:40.53,Default,,0,0,0,,First, what to do with Dieter?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.37,0:18:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if I go to the police...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.47,0:18:44.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't go with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.71,0:18:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I don't know much about\NJohan's sister because{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.08,0:18:53.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}she was left at an orphanage\Nin a different district.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.02,0:18:56.25,Default,,0,0,0,,A different orphanage...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.79,0:18:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.86,0:19:10.03,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a child that you\Nwant me to take in?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.17,0:19:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So, who are you? Why are you\Ncoming here at this hour?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.87,0:19:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I know it's an unreasonable request,\Nbut this kid...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.08,0:19:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I know that the kid is being abused.\NBut if I don't know who you are...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.78,0:19:27.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Umm...Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.88,0:19:32.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't take in a child from\Nsomeone so suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.29,0:19:38.66,Default,,0,0,0,,U-Umm...could this be the orphanage\Nthat took care of Anna Liebert?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.39,0:19:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Anna Liebert?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.60,0:19:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You know Anna Liebert?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.70,0:19:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,S-So Anna was here?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.60,0:19:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. How nostalgic...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.11,0:19:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,How is Anna doing? Is she well?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.18,0:19:54.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.41,0:19:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now, she's going\Nto Heidelberg University...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.28,0:20:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. She's doing well!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.18,0:20:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Anna was a nice girl...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.29,0:20:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew she was adopted by\NMr. Liebert of the Trade Commission
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.09,0:20:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,along with her twin brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.42,0:20:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Umm...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.43,0:20:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,What was his name?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.93,0:20:12.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Johan.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.03,0:20:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Johan, Johan.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.30,0:20:19.79,Default,,0,0,0,,They were very close,\Nbut I felt sorry for them
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.90,0:20:20.87,Default,,0,0,0,,when they were placed\Nin separate orphanages.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.30,0:20:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Those two were really alone\Nbefore they came here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.91,0:20:32.81,Default,,0,0,0,,When they were taken into custody\Nnear the border of Czechoslovakia,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.91,0:20:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,they were holding hands\Nas they walked.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.52,0:20:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,They both were shivering in the cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.35,0:20:44.09,Default,,0,0,0,,At first, Mr. Liebert only\Nwanted to adopt Johan.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.46,0:20:46.43,Default,,0,0,0,,But Johan wouldn't go\Nwithout his sister...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.66,0:20:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Thankfully, Anna got to be happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.63,0:20:53.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard that the conditions\Nof the orphanages
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.67,0:20:55.53,Default,,0,0,0,,of the east side were horrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.87,0:20:58.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We're not like 511 Kinderheim.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.87,0:20:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.72,0:21:14.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Inge, the bathroom isn't that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.42,0:21:16.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay? See?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.73,0:21:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Mommy...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.70,0:21:25.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all right. It's all right...\NThere's nothing to be afraid of.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.20,0:21:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Now...you can go to the bathroom\Nby yourself, can't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.34,0:21:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Those kids really did not know\Na parent's love.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.75,0:21:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You only need love in order to\Ndevelop as a person.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.82,0:21:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,As you say, the orphanages of\Nthe east side were quite horrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.66,0:21:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Even this place was once referred to\Nas Orphanage 47.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.03,0:21:58.83,Default,,0,0,0,,But we did what we could\Nso we wouldn't be controlled
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.93,0:22:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,by the government,\Neven just a little
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.00,0:22:04.97,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to avoid becoming\Nlike 511 Kinderheim.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.21,0:22:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a special orphanage\Nrun by both
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.01,0:22:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the Ministry of Health and Welfare\Nand the Ministry of the interior.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.31,0:22:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know what that means?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.22,0:22:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.62,0:22:18.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The real state of affairs\Nwas being managed by
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.12,0:22:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,the Ministry of the interior.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.42,0:22:25.29,Default,,0,0,0,,That place was...East Germany's\Nexperimental laboratory...
